to the editor re many in gop remain bullish in face of loss front page may 31 while i do not condone either senator james m jeffords 's defection from the republican party or the right wing response let 's stop the blame game as a lifelong republican a woman a moderate from the northeast and a 21 year veteran of congress let me offer my prescription to my party in a two party system in a country that is geographically and politically diverse we can be the majority party only if we find consensus and develop coalitions no moderates do n't want to steer the ship but we do deserve to be at the chart table when the navigation plans are developed this approach works the evidence is there the tax bill that has been passed and the strong education bill now moving through congress both bills are the product of consensus and compromise marge roukema member of congress 5th dist nj washington may 31 2001

